our “three es” energy environment and economic development continue reading greening the valley in the s tva turned selected farmers into experts on erosion control and asked them to pass the idea along to their neighbors before long agriculture in the tva region was on the road to recovery continue reading the mountaintop marvel scorned at the outset as a scheme worthy of rube goldberg tva’s pumpedstorage generating plant inside raccoon mountain became one of the engineering wonders of the tennessee valley continue reading share this page you are here home about tva about tva the tennessee valley authority is a corporate agency of the united states that provides electricity for business customers and local power distributors serving  million people in parts of seven southeastern states tva receives no taxpayer funding deriving virtually all of its revenues from sales of electricity in addition to operating and investing its revenues in its electric system tva provides flood control navigation and land management for the tennessee river system and assists local power companies and state and local governments with economic development and job creation find out more about our service commitment our leadership our executive leadership oversees all tva strategy policy and operations on a daily basis learn about their service and dedication to the tennessee valley board of directors executives advisory councils tva’s board of directors created an opportunity for the public and private sectors to give input on the region’s pressing energy and environmental stewardship issues regional energy resource council regional resource stewardship council tva history tva has long been a fundamental force in the prosperity of the tennessee valley since its beginning in  here you can read about its decadebydecade impacts in the areas of energy production environmental stewardship and economic development community relations learn how tva supports the social and economic wellbeing of the communities in the tennessee valley region through its efforts in education human services and community enrichment volunteering at tva want to make a difference to the tennessee valley region volunteer at tva and be part of our mission of service—to provide regional environmental stewardship reliable power and economic development tva police the us tva police— —is a federally commissioned law enforcement agency dedicated to the protection of tva’s employees visitors and physical assets this includes tva public lands and lakes and the people who enjoy them information about tva tva at a glance tva in alabama tva in georgia tva in kentucky tva in mississippi tva in north carolina tva in tennessee tva in virginia   tva employees are your neighbors your friends and your family we happily serve the people of the valley today to generate a better tomorrow we live work and play here too click here to read our stories  want to be part of the tva story follow us and share your own experiences of life in the valley poweredbypeopleyouknow   investor relations investment in tva supports electricity environment and economic development of the tennessee valley guidelines and reports these documents govern tvas daily operations and report on how its doing ombudsman tva’s ombudsman provides an independent channel for mediating stakeholder complaints complaint resolution process if you have an issue regarding your electric service account youve been unable to resolve with your local power company tva may be able to help contact us contact information for tva’s corporate offices and emergency assistance lines back to top tva  careers javascript must be enabled for the correct page display skip to main content share this page you are here home careers careers at tva do you have a passion to serve others in a career that can make a real difference at tva we serve the people of the tennessee valley to make life better through our mission of the three es energy production environment