probate most of dont know a lot about the law of wills trusts or probateafter all theyre topics none of us really want to deal with making a will are lawyers optional most people dont need a lawyer to make their will heres why how much will a lawyer charge to write your will depending on where you live and how complicated your family and financial circumstances are a lawyer may charge anything from a few hundred to several thousand dollars for a will what a will wont do many kinds of property  perhaps some of the most valuable things you own  dont necessarily pass through your will here are some things you shouldnt expect to accomplish in your will making a living trust can you do it yourself many people dont need a lawyer to create a living trust renters  tenants rights more avoiding fights over deposits most deposit hassles involve disputes over “how clean is clean” or “what’s wear and tear” disputes over back rent or replacements are more rare unfortunately no statute or court opinion will give you a universally accepted standard for cleanliness or “normal” wear and tear smart landlords late rent fees the basics of late rent fees including limits on how much landlords can charge taxes more why you should file your taxes early whether youre owed a refund or not its a good idea to file your irs tax return early top personal tax deductions dont overlook any of these personal tax deductions  they make itemizing your deductions well worth it child tax credits children are expensive congress wants to encourage people to have kids by giving them special tax credits can you use form ez most people think that preparing tax returns is extremely complicated and difficult it can be but the tax returns for many taxpayers are very simple and easy to prepare related products more chapter  bankruptcy how to file for chapter  bankruptcy the new bankruptcy related ads need professional help  get debt relief now weve helped  clients find attorneys today zip code start how it works 